Phase 2 — BUILD

Objective: Construct a Minimum Viable Product (MVP) agent that can successfully execute the "happy path" of the designed workflow in a controlled development environment.

Core Question: "Can we make it work once, under perfect conditions?"

Phase 2 Activities and Deliverables

Activity Description Deliverable
Prompt Logic Design the system prompts, few-shot examples, chain-of-thought instructions, and fallback responses for each agent role. Prompts must be version-controlled. Prompt Library (Versioned in Git)
Tool Connectors Implement the actual connections to external systems. Preference: MCP Servers. If MCP is not available, build custom connectors with strict schema validation and error handling. Tool Integration Code (With unit tests for schema validation)
Orchestration Graph Build the workflow Directed Acyclic Graph (DAG) using the selected framework (LangGraph, CrewAI, AutoGen). Define nodes, edges, and conditional routing logic. Orchestration Configuration (YAML or Python code)
Memory Schema Implement the vector storage (e.g., Pinecone, Weaviate) and retrieval patterns. Configure the Knowledge Graph connection (e.g., Neo4j) if required. Memory Layer Code (Indexing and retrieval logic)
Observability Hooks Instrument the agent with tracing and logging. Every LLM call and tool invocation must be captured. Use OpenTelemetry standards where possible. Telemetry Integration (Connected to LangSmith, Langfuse, or Arize Phoenix)

Phase 2 Output

Deliverable Name: MVP Agent
The agent can execute the primary workflow path from start to finish in a sandboxed development environment.

Phase 2 Gate

Gate Name: Happy Path Execution
Requirement: Agent successfully completes the primary workflow for at least 10 consecutive runs in the development environment without a critical error.
Failure Protocol: Return to Build. Debug prompts or tool connections until Happy Path is stable.

