Phase 3 — EVALUATE

Objective: Apply rigorous, automated testing to determine if the agent is safe, accurate, and economically viable for production deployment.

Core Question: "Does this agent meet the contractual metrics defined in the Charter?"

Phase 3 Evaluation Metrics (The Non-Negotiable Gates)

This is the most critical phase for preventing the 40% cancellation rate. Organizations that "eyeball" evaluation deploy broken agents. Organizations that use this table survive budget reviews.

Metric Target Threshold Measurement Method Failure Consequence
Success Rate ≥ 70% Automated test suite on a representative sample of tasks (minimum n=500) Return to Build for prompt/tool refinement
Hallucination Rate ≤ 5% Factual verification against ground truth data (requires human annotation sample or verified golden dataset) Return to Build; increase RAG retrieval quality
Cost per Task Below Human Baseline Inference cost tracking (input/output tokens × model price) + tool call overhead Trigger economic review; consider model routing (Law 9)
