Phase 4 — DEPLOY

Objective: Introduce the agent to production workload incrementally, minimizing blast radius and validating real-world performance.

Core Question: "How do we release this agent without breaking the business?"

Phase 4 Deployment Stages (Canonical Rollout)

Stage Description Duration Traffic/Workload Success Criterion
1. Canary Release Deploy to a minimal slice of traffic or workload. This is a live experiment. 3-7 days 1-5% Zero Critical Incidents. No security flags or data corruption events.
2. Shadow Mode Critical Trust-Building Phase. Agent executes alongside human; the human's decision is used, but the agent's output is logged and compared silently. 1-2 weeks 100% (Silent Execution) Agent output matches human output ≥ 80% on non-escalated tasks.
3. Limited Rollout Agent takes control of the workflow for a designated subset of users or tasks. Human is available for escalations (≤10% per Phase 3). 2-4 weeks 25-50% Metrics hold above Phase 3 evaluation thresholds. Intervention Penalty (T_c) is measured.
4. Full Production Agent handles 100% of the designated workload. Monitoring (Phase 5) is active and alerting is configured. Ongoing 100% Continuous Monitoring Active. Breakeven Law (T_c < 0.5 T_h) is maintained.

Phase 4 Gate

Gate Name: Production Readiness Review (PRR)
Requirement: Each stage must pass its success criterion before proceeding to the next stage.
Failure Protocol for Shadow Mode: If agent output matches human < 80%, the agent is not yet competent. Return to Phase 3: EVALUATE to identify the gap between "test set" and "live reality." This is a common source of the 40% cancellation.

