🔹 Layer 6: DATA LAYER

Position: Foundation of Truth
Ownership: Chief Data Officer, Data Platform Teams
Lifecycle Phase Alignment: Phase 2 (Build - Memory Schema), Phase 5 (Monitor - Drift Detection)

Purpose

This layer operationalizes Law 5: Data Quality Limits Autonomy. It ensures that agents operate on fresh, accurate, and semantically meaningful data. Bad data at this layer leads to Autonomous Hallucination at Scale.

Canonical Components

Component Description Technology Examples
Data Quality Monitoring Automated validation of data freshness, completeness, and schema adherence. Great Expectations, Monte Carlo.
Semantic Layer A business-friendly abstraction over raw data tables (e.g., "Customer LTV" instead of SUM(table_x.col_y)). dbt Semantic Layer, Cube.dev.
Knowledge Graph A structured representation of entities and relationships within the enterprise. Neo4j, Amazon Neptune.
Vector Database Storage for embeddings used in semantic search and RAG. Pinecone, Weaviate, pgvector.
Access Control (Zero-Trust) Fine-grained, attribute-based access control (ABAC) ensuring agents only see data they are authorized to access. Immuta, Open Policy Agent (OPA).
Data Lineage Tracking the origin and transformation of data used by agents for auditability. OpenLineage, DataHub.

Data Readiness Assessment (Pre-Deployment Gate)

Before an agent enters Phase 4 (Deploy), the Data Layer must pass a readiness assessment:

· Data freshness is ≥ 95% for critical tables.
· Semantic layer definitions are validated with business stakeholders.
· Vector embeddings are updated within the defined TTL.
· Access controls have been tested for the agent's service account.

2026 Imperative

Address the 49-80% barrier: The majority of enterprises cite data quality as the primary blocker to agentic AI deployment. Investment in the Data Layer is the single highest-ROI activity in 2026.

